<br><br>
<br><br>
In October 2020, precipitation showed relatively consistent patterns across the continent, indicating wetter-than-average conditions over most of western Europe including the UK and Ireland. During the first week of October, storm Alex caused widespread and heavy precipitation across western Europe, with record breaking values and subsequent floods over regions of southern France and northern Italy. Central Europe, most of Scandinavia, and a longitudinal band stretching eastwards along the Baltic coast up to north-western Russia also experienced wetter conditions. Precipitation was also above average in the west of the Iberian Peninsula. Moving eastwards, the rest of the continent shows drier-than-average-conditions
<br><br>
