<h2>The weather in October 2020</h2>
<h3>Temperature deviations and extremes</h3>
<br><br>
Average temperatures were above average in northern and eastern Europe. Southwestern Europe experienced below average temperatures, especially the Iberian Peninsula, France, Italy and the Alpine Region. The last week of September 2020 and the first two weeks of October 2020 were the coldest such period since 1974 in France. Despite the below temperatures in the southwest, Europe as a whole saw its warmest October on record.
