<br><br>
<h3>Precipitation</h3>
Precipitation sums were above average for most parts of Europe, especially in Eastern Europe.
Various storms caused high 1-day precipitation sums (Figure 9 and 10 middle figures) in southern France, northern Italy and the Baltic Countries (Alex), the United Kingdom (Aiden), Portugal (Barbara) and eastern Germany, Czech Republic, Poland and Slovakia (Gisela).
Below average rainfall fell in Eastern Spain and Italy (except for the far north).
