<h3>Radiation and Cloudiness</h3>
The global radiation anomaly based on E-OBS (Figure 12) shows a positive anomaly in France except for the far southeast and negative anomaly in the southeast of France/ northwest of Italy and large parts of Northern and Eastern Europe. The incoming surface radiation based on Seviri/Mviri data (Figure 13) is above the average in the far south of Europe and in Ireland but below average in the rest of Europe, corresponding well with the the maps of monthly cloud cover (Figure 14).
